On 3/14/05 10:35 PM, "Richard Atwell" <ratwell(-at-)mac.com> wrote:

> My telescoping magnet isn't strong enough to pull the cam followers out of
> the Type 4 case the first time. If you've watched the Raby rebuild video his
> magnet can't cut it either. I'd like to buy a stronger one.
> 
> Does anyone know the weight of the cam followers? I'd like to buy a stronger
> magnet for the next engine job but I don't want one so strong that it
> becomes awkward to use (sticks to too many other parts).

Look for one by Ullman, they make a few good ones, I think I have one of
each of these. The middle size is perfect for pulling a lifter out of the
engine case.

http://www.newmantools.com/ullman/ull3.htm#ht

Lifter weight varies pretty widely from about 90gm to 120gm depending on
manufacturer and hydro or solid.


